column13: In the [GetName] religion the [GetScriptureName] tells the story of their God [GetHighGodName] whose arm was cut off by the cruel [GetRandomEvilGodName], the pieces of their arm became the land and their blood the sea, creating the world as we know it. [GetPresitTitles] sometimes cut off parts of their own body in attempt to be closer to [GetHighGodName].

The followers of the [GetName] faith believe that all the world is but a game between [GetHighGodName] and [GetRandomEvilGodName]. Due to this a lot of their religious rites and worship are centered around a complex boardgame, with the most successful players becoming [GetPriestTitle]s the rules of this sacred game are recorded in the [GetScriptureName].
This Bloodline is passed on through the female line.

If in a Matrilineal Marriage, a Patrilineal Bloodline will be inherited from the woman and a Matrilineal from the man. If a child has no known father and their mother has a Patrilineal Bloodline, they will inherit it. This does not prevent Bloodlines from being inherited as per their normal rules, it only acts as an additional way of inheritance.
This Bloodline is passed on through the male line.
Click to decrease campaign funds by 10. SHIFT-click to decrease by 100. CTRL-click to remove the funds entirely.
Consorts enjoy no special rights and can simply be set aside when no longer pleasing.
[Actor.GetTitledFirstNameWithNick] has set you aside. You are no longer their concubine!
Does NOT have a Pressed Claim on $TITLE$

Otto was crowned King of the Germans after the death of his father Henry I. Early in his reign he had to push back a rebellion by Duke Eberhard of Bavaria, as well as fight a war against Louis IV of West-Francia and Duke Gilbert of Lorraine. After securing peace in the war, Otto went on to fight for the Italian throne as well as push back the Hungarian threat in the east. In his later years, after his coronation as the Emperor of the Holy Roman Empire, he had to continue his struggles in Italy to keep his newfound empire under control. The Ottonian dynasty went on to control the empire for almost half a century after his death, until it finally ended with the demise of Henry II in 1024.

Hakon was one of the many many sons of Harald Fairhair, legendary king of Norway. When his brother Eirik took control of Norway, not many years passed until his despotic rule made him unpopular to the point of rebellion. Hakon who had been raised by King √Üthelstan of England was sent back home to Norway to take over the rule of the kingdom. As a christian in a very pagan country, he had a long and tenuous rule over the many norwegian tribes. Throughout his rule he was threatened by the Danish king who supported the claims of his grandsons, the sons of his half-brother Eirik. In the end Hakon fell as he repelled the Danes at the Battle of Fitjar, and was succeeded by his nephew Harald II Greycloak.

As the third grand prince of the Hungarians and the successor to the legendary √Årp√°d, Zolta led their people for several decades in the early 10th century. Throughout this period the Hungarians were feared raiders who travelled across all of Europe, from Byzantium to C√≥rdoba. After his death in the year 950, only a few years passed until Otto I beat back the Hungarian raiders in the Battle of Lechfeld, putting an end to their tyranny.

Abu'l-Qasim Sa'id started the Qarmatian faith centered around his capital in al-Bahrein when the Fatimid Caliphate rose in the west. After his father's demise, Abu Tahir continued as the new leader and became infamous throughout the Arabian Peninsula for his raids into Egyptian and Abbasid lands. In 930 he pillaged Mecca, murdered the many pilgrims who had travelled there and stole the Black Stone. After this sacrilege the Qarmatians became even more hated throughout the whole Muslim world, but that did not deter Abu Tahir as he continued the raids and assaults on his neighbours, until he finally died a decade later.

Al-Qaim followed his father, Caliph al-Mahdi, as he settled down in Ifriqiya and established the Fatimid Caliphate. In direct opposition to the Abbasid Caliphate in Baghdad, they filled the room left behind as the Abbasids had lost control of their peripheral regions. Early in al-Qaim's reign, a large rebellion rose up in the west led by Abu Yazid. For several years the Fatimid armies were pushed back, as the rebellion grew ever closer to their capital in Mahdia. After al-Qaim's death, his son and successor al-Mansur finally managed to beat the rebellion back and take control of their lands once again. The dynasty would later go on to invade Ikhshidid Egypt and establish Cairo as the new capital of their Caliphate.

As the son of Edward the Elder, he gained the Kingdom of Mercia after the death of his father, and Wessex after the death of his brother only weeks afterwards. Waging war against the Norsemen in York, √Üthelstan pushed northwards and took the city in 927, becoming the first king of a truly united England. Ten years later, in 937, a coalition led by the Kings of Scotland, Strathclyde, and Dublin waged war against √Üthelstan, which ended with the Battle of Brunanburh. With a decisive victory it seemed √Üthelstan had finally secured his rule in England, but only two years later he died and was succeeded by his half-brother Edmund.

A beacon of virtue and wisdom, [Root.GetTitledFirstName] has acquired immortal fame by dedicating years of [Root.GetHerHis] rule to reach a deeper understanding of the word of [Root.Religion.GetName] and of the truths hidden within our holy texts.\nRiding through an initial tide of controversy, the [Root.GetTitle] of [Root.PrimaryTitle.GetName] was able to establish a court of scholars and theologian, filled with endless disquisitions over the highest matters which will surely prove instrumental to lead us to gain a better understanding of this world and the ones beyond.
How unfortunate that [From.GetFirstName] will no longer be able to fulfill [From.GetHerHis] duties as my guardian. Perhaps [From.GetHerHis] successor will be kinder to me.

Against all odds, the children of Christ have succeeded in their unlikely quest to reconquer Jerusalem! \nHosts of archangels in shining armors and flaming swords have been reported to have descended upon the walls of the holy city during the final battle, smiting the infidels, turning the defenders' weapons into rust and melting their eyes out.\n[From.GetFirstName] now rules over the Kingdom of Heaven, and few doubts that it was through divine intervention that [From.GetSheHe] was put there.
[From.GetTitledFirstName] dislikes me already, perhaps I should focus my hatred towards a different target?

Several Hellenic gods are associated with earth and prosperity. [GetDemetraCeresName] oversees the harvest, [GetAphroditeVenusName] is associated with fertility, [GetHermesMercuryName] to roads and trading, and [GetHestiaVestaName], one of the most beloved Roman goddesses, to hearth and family.

Apollo takes a very prestigious spot in Hellenic mythology, being associated with reason, arts and medicine. His twin sister [GetArtemisDianaName] on the other hand tends to have humbler, more secretive followers, being associated with night and nature.

While avoiding to be forgotten entirely is my primary concern, it is also equally important for me to think about how do I wish posterity to think of me. How can I make sure that when I die, future generations will speak in awe and wonder about my accomplishments as [Root.GetTitle], and feel inspired to emulate me?
In order to immortalize my name I must leave an indelible mark on [Root.PrimaryTitle.GetName], improve my realm beyond what all my predecessors dared to accomplish...

The shamans carve the final details on the surface of the mask, whispering ancient spells to bind the ethereal spirit to it for centuries to come. When they are satisfied with their work, they turn around and offer me the artifact, assuring me that I will be able to access to its power by wearing it in battle.

The conversion of [converting_king.Capital.GetName] starts on a cold morning.\nThe Bishop leading [sponsoring_king.GetTitledFirstName]'s embassy meets you at a river near the city. Your faithful vassals stand beside you, while the rest of your subjects wait their turn behind them, looking still visibly confused. The Bishop recites a few verses from [catholic.GetScriptureName] before you lead your vassals into the river. As you pass the [sponsoring_king.Religion.GetName] priests they baptize you, one after the other, in the cold water. It takes some prodding from the guards to convince the peasants to follow you into the water, but, after a while, the entire crowd stands soaked and shaking by the riverside, just in time to watch the priests and their helpers drop your old idols into the waves.\n"As the false visages are swallowed by the tides" the Bishop proclaims, "may their memory forever be banished from your soul."

To [Root.GetTitledFirstName],
I shall be glad to legitimize your divine right to rule, as soon as you recognize that the Church is no servant to any King or Emperor, but instead watches over the salvation of the souls of all Christians, regardless of their stature. 

Sincerely,
[From.GetTitledFirstName]
With the wicked ruler forced into exile, the Pope has finally accepted to crown me [Root.GetTitle]. It is time to sheathe our weapons and let the celebrations begin.

The Christian Pope has decided to call one of his lackeys to arms against me, in an attempt to reclaim some of the Italian lands currently under my control. [From.GetTitledFirstName] has just declared war against me on the Pope's behalf.

Only a few more days before I am crowned [Root.GetTitle] before God and all my subjects. My court has been already filled with all my distinguished guests, both vassals and foreign dignitaries come to bear witness to this fundamental moment of my reign. Such a lavish ceremony with so prestigious guests is a rare spectacle to behold even amongst royalty.

Organizing such a monumental ceremony has given me the chance to better know the rulers of the realms neighboring [Root.PrimaryTitle.GetName]. Maintaining healthy relationships with my Christian peers is fundamental to ensure the future peace and prosperity of my realm. [potential_friend.GetTitledFirstName] in particular seems like a [potential_friend.GetManWoman] I could really trust...

The night at [From.GetTitledFirstName]'s court took a strange turn when our host decided to call some of the clergymen and scholars at the nobles' table, engaging with them in a long discussion about theology. I did not expect this feast to turn into a lesson about Christianity, but...

I kneel before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as a host of Electors and vassals surrounds us in complete silence. The Pope blesses me as he prepares himself to place the Imperial Crown upon my head and proclaim me [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of the Romans by grace of God, and protector of all Christendom.

[coronation_ruler.GetTitledFirstName] kneels before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] host of Electors and vassals surrounds them in complete silence. The Pope blesses [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] before placing the Imperial Crown upon [coronation_ruler.GetFirstName]'s head and proclaiming [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of the Romans by grace of God, and protector of all Christendom.

I kneel before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as host of vassals surrounds us in complete silence. The Pope blesses me before placing the Imperial Crown upon my head and proclaiming me [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

[coronation_ruler.GetTitledFirstName] kneels before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] host of vassals surrounds them in complete silence. The Pope blesses [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] before placing the Imperial Crown upon [coronation_ruler.GetFirstName]'s head and proclaiming [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

[coronation_ruler.GetTitledFirstName] kneels before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] host of vassals surrounds them in complete silence. The Pope gives the child an encouraging smile as [coronation_priest.GetSheHe] blesses [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] and places the Imperial Crown upon [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] head, proclaiming [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

I kneel before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as a host of vassals surrounds us in complete silence. The Pope blesses me and places the Royal Crown upon my head, proclaiming me [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

[coronation_ruler.GetTitledFirstName] kneels before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] host of vassals surrounds them in complete silence. The Pope blesses [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] and places the Royal Crown upon [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] head, proclaiming [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

[coronation_ruler.GetTitledFirstName] kneels before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] host of vassals surrounds them in complete silence. The Pope gives the child an encouraging smile as [coronation_priest.GetSheHe] blesses [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] and places the Royal Crown upon [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] head, proclaiming [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

I kneel before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as a host of vassals surrounds us in complete silence. The [coronation_priest.GetTitle] blesses me and places the crown upon my head, proclaiming me [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

[coronation_ruler.GetTitledFirstName] kneels before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] host of vassals surrounds them in complete silence. The [coronation_priest.GetTitle] blesses [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] and places the crown upon [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] head, proclaiming [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

[coronation_ruler.GetTitledFirstName] kneels before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] as [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] host of vassals surrounds them in complete silence. The [coronation_priest.GetTitle] gives the child an encouraging smile as [coronation_priest.GetSheHe] blesses [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] and places the Royal Crown upon [coronation_ruler.GetHerHis] head, proclaiming [coronation_ruler.GetHerHim] [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

I kneel before [coronation_priest.GetTitledFirstName] in the empty hall of my palace and, after a quick blessing, the [coronation_priest.GetTitle] summarily and places the crown upon my head, proclaiming me [coronation_ruler.GetTitle] of [coronation_ruler.PrimaryTitle.GetName] by grace of God.

A month has passed since I gave birth to little [From.GetFirstName]. As is tradition, I should undergo my Churching, as any good Christian mother does, and rejoin the Holy Church now that my body has been cleansed of all impurities.

[Root.GetHaruspexName] cuts the prisoner open. While the man's heart is immolated, the diviner starts rummaging through his entrails. The response is quite clear. The gods favor our cause in the war to come! The troops will fight with renewed strength now that they know for sure that our victory has been ordained from the heavens.

[Root.GetHaruspexName] cuts the prisoner open. While the man's heart is immolated, the diviner starts rummaging through his entrails. The signs are not entirely clear, but the diviner assures me that there was no signs of the Fates opposing our war. Our troops will surely be comforted by knowing that the gods are not against them.

[Root.GetHaruspexName] cuts the prisoner open. While the man's heart is immolated, the diviner starts rummaging through his entrails. Unfortunately, the response from the diviner is not as positive as I hoped. There are clear signs that the gods are not in favor of this war. This news will not be good for morale...

[Root.GetHaruspexName] cuts the prisoner open. While the man's heart is immolated, the diviner starts rummaging through his entrails. The response is terrible. Not only are the gods against us in this war but, according to the signs interpreted by the diviner, they seem to be favoring our enemies!

I have recently found myself talking with [other_combatant.GetTitledFirstName], often about [other_combatant.GetRootMatchingPersonalityStreak]. I have to laugh, however, when the [other_combatant.GetManWoman] attempts to compliment my fighting technique ‚Äì we both know that I didn't do very well, last time we sparred.

Ever since the battle of [battlefield_location.GetName], I have had a hard time [GetPostBattleStruggle]. Tonight, as I go to sleep, I can hardly breathe and I wake up thrashing in my bed from the nightmares.

To the valiant [Root.GetTitledFirstName],
After your display of strength in the duel, we would be honored to invite you into our ranks.

Signed,
[From.GetTitledFirstName]

To the honorable [Root.GetTitledFirstName],
After your display of strength in the duel, we would be honored to invite you into our ranks.

Signed,
[From.GetTitledFirstName]

To the brave [Root.GetTitledFirstName],
After your display of strength in the duel, we would be honored to invite you into our ranks.

Signed,
[From.GetTitledFirstName]

My history in battle is known to many, but there are still those who could benefit from learning more about my experiences. "Like that time you chopped someone's head off?" [fellow_member.GetTitledFirstName] asks, in response to my idea. "A feast, where you regale your court with the stories!" [fellow_member.GetSheHe] continues. I consider the spirits it could lift, as I soon depart for [target_title.GetName].
[target.GetTitledFirstName] made an impression in [home_capital.GetName] once. I could use this to boost morale before I run off into [target_title.GetName].
My travel companion and fellow [Root.GetSocietyRank] [FromFrom.GetTitledFirstName] has been taken prisoner by [From.GetTitledFirstName], after challenging [From.GetHerHim] to one on one combat...!

Charging into the glade, I am itching for a fight. My opponent simply waits, one hand resting on [other_combatant.GetHersHis] [other_combatant.GetDuelWeapon]. I draw closer, thinking this is going to be fun! The [target_ruler.Capital.GetRegionalBigAnimal] dead on the ground, I raise my own weapon, about to let out my battle cry. Then I hear the desperate roar of the animal behind me and then... nothing.

The whole area is filled with people, looking like they come from all the different corners of the world. I see another [Root.GetCultureAdj] looking at me, and giving me a small nod before [Root.GetSheHeOpp] disappears in the crowd. I never knew  [pilgrimage_destination.province_saint.GetFirstNameWithNick] was this popular or well known. Though it is stressful, I finally get my moment to stand in front of the grave, and feel the blessed aura of the Saint.

There is a couple of other pilgrims around, but they all look relatively local to the area. I walk over to the grave, and look down at the small statue of the saint as well as the stone commemorating the life of the saint. It has been a long journey to get to [pilgrimage_destination.GetName], and I finally get to look upon the blessed burial site of  [pilgrimage_destination.province_saint.GetFirstNameWithNick].

The burial site is completely void of people, not a single soul to be seen. I look around for it, almost sure I am at the wrong place for a moment, and then I see the small grave. It looks overgrown and deserted, and I take some time to tidy the place up before I finally sit down in prayer to [Root.Religion.GetHighGodName]. It is almost like  [pilgrimage_destination.province_saint.GetFirstNameWithNick] is here and prays with me.

Constantinople falls to great cheers from the [From.Religion.GetName] Crusaders. The rest of the world weeps as the last lingering memories of the Roman Empire shatters. The former Emperor [FromFrom.GetDynName] has run off to [FromFrom.Capital.GetName] to try and restore what remains of the Empire.

[Root.GetByzantineRefugeeText]Now [e_latin_empire.Holder.GetTitledFirstName] sits on the throne in Constantinople. [e_latin_empire.Holder.GetSheHeCap] has declared [e_latin_empire.Holder.GetHerselfHimself] the new ruler of the Greek Empire, and will rule with both Greek and Latin traditions in mind.

Only time will tell, if the [From.Religion.GetName]s will be remembered as the ones who broke the [From.Religion.GetGroupName] Bulwark, or the ones who restored Constantinople to greatness.

Constantinople falls to great cheers from the [From.Religion.GetName] Crusaders. The rest of the world weeps as the last lingering memories of the Roman Empire shatters. The old Emperor [FromFrom.GetDynName] has run off to [FromFrom.Capital.GetName] to try and restore what remains of the Empire.

[Root.GetByzantineRefugeeText]Now [e_latin_empire.Holder.GetTitledFirstName] sits on the throne in Constantinople. [e_latin_empire.Holder.GetSheHeCap] has declared [e_latin_empire.Holder.GetHerselfHimself] the new ruler of the Greek Empire, and will rule with both Greek and Latin traditions in mind.

Only time will tell, if the [From.Religion.GetName]s will be remembered as the ones who broke the [From.Religion.GetGroupName] Bulwark, or the ones who restored Constantinople to greatness.

The traitorous Duke Giselbert of Lorraine left our service after the death of our esteemed father King Henry. Now they have turned to the protection of the Karlings in West Francia, asking them for aid against us.\n\nNot only have they forsaken their ancient service to our rule, but our spies tells us Gilbert has been conspiring with traitorous lords of the realm. The insult is too much to bear at this point, and it is about time we took back what is rightfully ours.

Reports from our scouts in the east confirms our suspicions, Otto is preparing for an attack on our lands. Long has the king of the Germans sought for a justifiable reason to try and force Lorraine back under his sovereignty, but now it seems he has thrown caution to the wind.\n\nIt is time to gather our men and protect ourselves. Lorraine is ours, and we will make sure the Germans pay dearly for every step they take into it.

My younger brother Otto has been a thorn in my side from a young age, and it only escalated after he was made primary heir to our father Heinrich. He has repeatedly withheld titles that should be rightfully mine, and given them away to others instead.\n\nFrom my correspondence with the other lords of the realm, it is clear I am not the only one who feels slighted by my tyrannical sibling. Particularly the lords of Franconia and East Frisia are sure to join me, if I am to make a declaration of war upon Otto.

The elder bastard of Heinrich, Thankmar, have declared war upon our liege, his younger brother Otto. It has been obvious to most that the man has felt slighted by his sibling for quite a while now, and it comes as no surprise when one of his messengers arrive in [Root.Capital.GetName].\n\nAfter a long and tiring speech, the messenger finally asks if we can bring word back to his lord that we will join the rebellion. Though we have never particularly cared for Otto either, it all seems a bit much. Though it is a good chance to lessen the authority of the Saxon Kings.

It seems my beloved older brother Thankmar has raised an army to topple my rule over the Germans. Though a surprise to everyone at court, the man has always had an ambitious streak.

After a couple of minutes to process all of it, I give the order to prepare our troops to fight our fellow Saxons. It is a tragedy that it has come to this, but it seems like there is no other choice.

Let us just hope there will not be more lords flocking to his cause.

After a long and tiresome war, our victory has finally been ensured, as Otto is brought to me in chains. He looks tired and saddened by all of it, but I will not let him spoil the celebrations.\n\nThe lords now look to me for guidance, as the new king of the Germans. Lately, however, I have felt like it might be time to put an end to the Saxon rule over foreign lands. Maybe it is time to return to time of old, before the Carolingians and Merohingians gathered all the Germans under one rule.

After crushing the armies of his brother Otto, King Thankmar of the Germans has declared that the tribes of old will once more be ruled by their own. No longer will a Saxon King rule over foreign people.

Unmaking the centuries of authority built up by the Carolingians, Merohingians and even those of his own family, he has simply let go off the old bonds binding the dukes of the southern lands to himself.

Franconia, Swabia, Thuringia and Bavaria now look to their own lords to rule them in these uncertain times. It is said the legacy of Charlemagne has been buried for good.

I look at Thankmar, as he is brought to me in chains. My once great older brother looks haggard and tired as he stands in front of me. I finally ask the guards to take him away, for now.

No celebrations will be had, as this has been nothing but a tragedy for all of us. Though it was an appalling end, it was most likely the only conclusion we could have to this conflict.

With the problematic lords of the realm quelled, it is time to look towards the future.

Under the horrendous leadership of [italian_king.GetTitledFirstName], Italy has become a shadow of what it once was. The great legacy of the Romans and their descendants have been shattered by the civil wars and the chaos of the last decades.\n\nNow many of the minor Italian lords under his leadership have sent us emissaries asking for aid. They supposedly miss the days when they were under our distant rule. If we want to raise the banners of Charlemagne once more, the Kingdom of Italy will be essential in securing our recognition as true descendants of his empire.

The King of the Germans to our north, Otto, have declared war upon us. He loudly claim it is for the best of the Italian people, and pretends that he is liberating Italy from the rule of [italian_king.GetTitledName].\n\nThe Germans are preparing to pass through the Alps, and put an end to the chaos that has embroiled Italy once and for all. Who will stand against them and treat them like invaders, and who will embrace them like old neighbors and friends?

As the King of the Germans and with the Kingdom of Italy in our hands, few dispute our potential claim to Charlemagne's fame and empire. All that is missing, is our official proclamation of such a thing. Our advisors and friends are looking for us to give the word. Our chamberlain has hinted that he is ready to prepare a coronation any day now.\n\nIs it time to truly grasp our long-awaited fate? Will we raise the banners of Charlemagne once more, and declare ourselves the Emperor of the Holy Roman Empire?

In a beautiful ceremony in [From.Capital.GetName], Otto has invited friends, allies and enemies from near and far to take part as he is crowned the Emperor of the West. After quelling the lords who tried to oppose him early in his rule, and taking back the lands of his father piece by piece, few are left to oppose the king at this point.\n\nWith the banners of Charlemagne raised once more, and the authority of the long-lost empire at his back, Otto has done what nobody expected of him when he started his tumultuous rule. Now what is he planning to do next?

The Shias under the rule of [sultan_egypt.GetTitledName] have long suffered from being treated different to their Sunni neighbors, and lately it has gotten even worse. Stories of families being run out of or murdered in their homes have been told back to us, and now they are looking for someone to help them out.\n\nSeveral messengers, traders and merchants have come to [Root.Capital.GetName] to seek our aid, begging us to intervene. Egypt has long been an area that we have wished to influence, and this could be an opportunity to do just that.

The name 'West-Frisia' is a relic of times past, when the Frisians had presence in these lands. With them driven out and replaced by mighty Dutch, people have begun calling our realm 'Holland' instead, after the forested lands that form the center of the duchy. Perhaps it is time for us to embrace the change and use the new name in our records?

The lands north of the Rhine delta were once ruled by a mighty Frisian kingdom, but with their presence a distant memory, 'Holland' has become the accepted term for their duchy. [From.GetBestName] has encouraged the transition, and will be using it in [From.GetHerHis] official records from this moment forward.

After the failed revolt of [From.GetBestName] has finally been put down, [geldern_holder.GetTitledName] has brought forward a petition to your court to be installed as the ruler of Hamaland in the traitor's stead. [geldern_holder.GetSheHeCap], a claimant to Hamaland, seems a skilled and trustworthy fellow, and would no doubt be an asset to the realm.

After the failed rebellion of [FromFrom.GetBestName], a baron from Geldern has won the favor of [From.GetBestName], and [geldern_holder.GetSheHe] has been elevated to higher nobility. [geldern_holder.GetSheHeCap] now rules in the land formerly known as Chamavia.

A representative of the newly expanded city of Breda is making demands of you. They want their status as the main population center of the county of Toxandria to be recognized. The Toxandri were a tribe as mighty as any other, but the people have been extinct for centuries. Perhaps it is time to do away with this relic of a name, and honor Breda instead?

[From.GetBestName] has elected to refer to [From.GetHerHis] county of Toxandria by the name of its most populous city, Breda, from this moment onwards. The burghers are much pleased by the recognition and have held a feast in the honor of [From.GetTitledFirstName].

A representative of the newly expanded city of Kleve is making demands of you. They want their status as the main population center of the county of Hattuaria to be recognized. The Chattuarii were a tribe as mighty as any other, but the people have been extinct for centuries. Perhaps it is time to do away with this relic of a name, and honor Kleve instead?

On the 7th of August 936, Otto I was crowned King of the Germans. He initiated his arduous campaign to crush his rivals and reconquer the lost territory in Italy to reform the Holy Roman Empire. The Magyars settled down in the Carpathian Basin and began to make their mark on the world as they conquered and pillaged their neighbors, becoming feared across Europe. In the north the Christians were trying to push into the Scandinavian Peninsula to start converting the pagan kings, but the Germanic faith still stood strong among the vikings. In Baghdad far to the south-east, the ancient Abbasid Caliphate that once ruled an empire stretching from Persia to Hispania finally fell to infighting, left only with the heartland of their former empire. And on the shores of Africa a new rival rose up in the form of the Fatimid Caliphate, ready to fill the vacant regions left behind by their adversary.

Welcome to Crusader Kings II. We see that you are a newcomer to the game, so we hope you have fun exploring all the strategic and dynastic challenges that await you. The King's Journey is a new way of exploring the world of Crusader Kings and will help you earn special in-game rewards. Crusader Kings is a very open-ended game, but these Ruler Challenges give you specific goals to aim for. Ruler Challenges encourage you to focus your efforts, and may, in some cases, help you learn some parts of the game more quickly. But CK2 is an open game - don't feel bound by our rules!

Welcome back to Crusader Kings II! You have fought many wars and led many dynasties to greatness. With The King's Journey we have some new challenges for you to play. The Ruler Challenges present you with a new realm with a specific objective to achieve. Completing the challenges will earn special rewards to enhance your Crusader Kings experience. Here is your chance to try new worlds and new ways of play in our infinite medieval sandbox.

County cultures are randomized in a way that keeps individual cultures and groups together, but appearing in different places around the map. Cultures like Roman and Han are included.
